		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jun 4th 4:13 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=105372368737452&num=3&page=0&post=1&replyto=105475518013041"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=105475518013041></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=192210"><span id=>chicotwelve</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />4 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=chicotwelve&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>As you've noticed by now, the bard is a fairly complicated class to play well, which is why you see so many bad bards running around training people. However, there are some good ones out there and i count myself lucky to be somewhere around the middle. Now, you want to know what stats you need when shopping for gear, and that really depends on what type of bard you consider yourself to be. As stated above, bards are part melee, so you really cant ignore any of your melee stats, specially early in the game when you rely more on your arm for damage output since you wont be getting decent dots till around your 40's. I didnt have much help when i was starting my career, so i messed everything up and had a hard time leveling, but looking back i would have put more focus on STR DEX and INT, as well as CHA. STA and AGI are really nice to have, but remember that a group that expects a bard to tank is not a group you want to be in, there are classes who specialize in tanking.. let them take the hits. You wont be using your mana till you start using your lvl 39 charm song, so INT is something you can leave alone for a later time if you dont feel like bothering with it just yet. And yes, stay away from AoE songs if you can, they usualy have a weak effect and all you get for your trouble is more aggro than you need. Well, thats my opinion on the subject, I hope it helps some. Visit those sites above, they really are a fountain of information.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
